name: Panko Parmesan Salmon
description: Of all the recipes I make, this one is my husband's favorite for salmon. It's made with panko, or Japanese bread crumbs, which are very light and crunchy, mixed with Parmesan cheese. It's baked in the oven until the panko is nice and toasted.
author: Dianne

name: Million-Dollar Spaghetti
description: The perfect combination of pasta, ground beef, and cream cheese mixture. Unbelievably good! Serve with garlic bread and salad. Enjoy!
author: Coqui30

name: Lemon Panko Crusted Salmon
description: I love serving this salmon with a side of glazed baby carrots and garlic feta mashed potatoes. It's a quick, yet healthy meal that will satisfy your hunger
author: thedailygourmet

name: Buttered Biscuits
description: These biscuits are very easy to make and are very good.
author: Debbie Rowe

name: Cinnamon Bread I
description: This is a lovely way to start off your morning when you want a little something different than your usual. Note: If you don't have buttermilk you may substitute milk with 1 tablespoon vinegar to measure 1 cup.
author: Carol

name: Asian Salmon
description: Wild salmon is marinated and baked in an Asian-inspired soy and sesame sauce, served with hot cooked rice.
author: Lynseey

name: Salmon Dip
description: One of my favorite recipes! I have had many ask for this recipe. It is always one of the first things gone when I bring it to a barbeque.
author: RTR.MAR

name: Chicken Marsala Florentine
description: This is a gorgeous chicken dish with sun-dried tomatoes, spinach, and mushrooms. It is so wonderful when served with garlic mashed potatoes. It tastes fantastic!
author: SHANOU

name: Grilled Bacon-Wrapped Chicken Tenders
description: The perfect marriage of smoky and sweet flavors is what you'll get when you use the outdoor grill to cook up these chicken tenders! I like to use center-cut bacon since it is leaner and less likely to cause flare-ups. I find cutting the bacon lengthwise, and then using the thin strips to wrap the bacon, is much easier than trying to wrap using a wide strip. Use your favorite BBQ rub on the chicken!
author: France C

name: Ginger-Chicken Stir Fry
description: Stir fries require very little cooking time and you can pretty much use any vegetables you like, but the star of this one is the ginger. This dish is quick and easy to make, but get all of your ingredients together (including mixing the sauce) before you start cooking because everything happens fast! Serve with rice, and garnish with sliced green onions.
author: lutzflcat

name: Grilled Chile-Cilantro-Lime Chicken
description: This easy chile-cilantro-lime chicken is salty, sweet, sour, and spicy. It's great on salads, with rice, or in burritos and wraps!
author: boltfan

name: Sofrito Chicken
description: Chicken thighs are simmered with sofrito and other seasonings until they fall apart. Serve with some yellow rice and beans for a delicious Spanish-style meal.
author: My Hot Southern Mess
